JDK - Java Development Kit (Oracle which owns Java). It has two main tools -> JRE AND JAVAC
JRE - Java Runtime Environment - Includes all the code behind the built-in functions and variable types.
JRE -> It includes JVM - Java Virtual Machine which allows java code to run on any machine or platform. JVM is a downlodable machine.  
Javac - Java Compiler -> It translates code into computer understandable language which is (byte code)(0/1) 

JAVA Code -> Javac(Compiler) -> ByteCode -> JVM -> Machine Code.
JVM converts the byte code into different machine codes it is on like windows, ios, mobile etc

